				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I had this spell given to me by a wonderful cleric who got it with a parchment.
<br />

<br />
So let me get this straight.
<br />

<br />
Reclaim will now return a constant amount regardless of Pet HP.
<br />

<br />
CoR does good burst damage then goes in to melee
<br />

<br />
He rarely AE's
<br />

<br />
So casting him and reclaiming him after he spends his load would effectively turn him into a new kind of Rage of Zomm. Good burst damage for a while then most of the mana cost back allowing us to cast him again for more burst damage. We nuke while he nukes, and throw in a Malo to help the nukes land.
<br />

<br />
With kindle, and on fights that have 30 seconds between pulls, he could sit and med back a lot of mana, making him useful there again.
<br />

<br />
Seems to me like CoR is a very underutilized aspect of what could make some great Mage DPS. My question though is where are the parses?  Is it possible to log mage pet casting damage?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
